quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  9,87,"They are content to be with those helpless who stay behind<sup>71</sup>; their hearts have been sealed, so that they do not understand.","[71] They are mainly women."
  9,88,"But the Messenger and those who believe with him strive with their wealth and their lives. It is they who will have all kinds of good, and it is they who are successful.",""
  9,89,"Allah has prepared for them gardens under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever; that is the supreme triumph.",""
  9,90,"Some of the Bedouins came with excuses, seeking to be exempted, while others who lied to Allah and His Messenger stayed behind. Those who disbelieved among them will be afflicted with a painful punishment.",""
  9,91,"There is no blame on the weak, the sick, or those who have nothing to spend, as long as they are sincere to Allah and His Messenger. There is no blame on those who do good, and Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.",""
  9,92,"Nor is there any blame on those who came to you asking you for mounts to take them along, and you said, “I can find no mounts for you;” they turned away with their eyes overflowing with tears out of grief that they had nothing to spend.",""
  9,93,"Blame is only on those who ask you for exemption even though they are affluent. They are content to stay behind with the helpless<sup>72</sup>, and Allah has sealed their hearts so they do not know.","[72] i.e., women who stayed home."
